      {
        "id": 2790235,
        "name": "Shay h arnoy",
        "username": "Shay_h_arnoy",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/b9e5f3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-12T23:40:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/4/4f12a4e22d562f86ca4e3d18cc0affcfb2516fa8.gif\" width=\"78\" height=\"40\" alt=\"newhere\" title=\"[new-here.gif]\"></p>\n<p>I am currently exploring wines of Burgundy, trying to keep budget in check while figuring out the best producers, QPR, villages, and vineyards for my taste.  I am especially a sucker for deals and coupons, however, many of the deal a day sites (WineText, LastBottle, etc\u2026) tend to have more obscure producers that may be of variable quality.</p>\n<p>I bought the Coates Wines of Burgundy book <a href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=8wGVSrtn_MYC&amp;newbks=0&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=coates+burgundy&amp;hl=en&amp;source=newbks_fb#v=onepage&amp;q=coates%20burgundy&amp;f=false\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Coates Wines of Burgundy book</a> and in it he ranks the producers and top premier cru vineyards. I found these rankings incomplete (and a bit outdated from 2008) but still very helpful when used alongside CellarTracker.  I digitized the star ranking from his appendix and have been using it for quick reference.  I thought folks on this board might find it useful as I have.</p>\n<p>Feel free to use the sheet or comment on it:  <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1agS0k_7gCOrgUUjHqUANo2f3AR-cYHib22SbfJvO8oA/edit?usp=sharing\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Burgundy Rankings</a></p>\n<p>Let me know if its taboo from a copyright/board etiquette perspective.  To be clear, I encourage everyone to buy the book as the details are often more useful than the stars <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">.</p>\n<p>Let me know if this is helpful!</p>",
